verbs.description: clicket (third-person singular simple present clickets, present participle (UK) clicketting or (US) clicketing, simple past and past participle (UK) clicketted or (US) clicketed)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, of a fox or foxes) To be in oestrus; to copulate.
examples: The sound of the clicketting foxes was unmistakable.

description: Old French cliquet (“the latch of a door”). See click.

entries.meaning: (UK, dialect) The knocker of a door.

examples: He carried always the small silver clicketWith which, as pleased him, he'd unlock the gate.
